## Summary

`@mem0/openclaw-mem0` v`0.4.0` supported a `userMapping` config key for multi-user OpenClaw deployments. In `1.0.4`, that key is rejected by the plugin schema with an `additional properties` / unknown key error, and the runtime behavior for mapping session keys to per-user Mem0 identities is gone.

This breaks a real multi-user OpenClaw use case where a single deployment serves multiple household users and relies on session-key-to-user mapping to prevent memory bleed between people.

## Why this matters

For multi-user or household deployments, this is not just convenience. It is a privacy boundary.

Without `userMapping` (or an equivalent replacement), memories from different people can collapse into a shared Mem0 user scope unless the operator splits deployments or uses a custom fork.

## Affected versions

- Works in: `@mem0/openclaw-mem0@0.4.0`
- Broken in: `@mem0/openclaw-mem0@1.0.4`

## Reproduction

Use a config that worked in `0.4.0`, for example:

```json
{
  "plugins": {
    "slots": {
      "memory": "openclaw-mem0"
    },
    "entries": {
      "openclaw-mem0": {
        "enabled": true,
        "config": {
          "mode": "open-source",
          "userId": "davidson-family",
          "autoRecall": true,
          "autoCapture": true,
          "topK": 5,
          "searchThreshold": 0.3,
          "userMapping": {
            "agent:main:web_chris_*": "chris",
            "agent:main:web_caroline_*": "caroline",
            "agent:main:web_shared_house": "household"
          },
          "oss": {
            "embedder": {
              "provider": "ollama",
              "config": {
                "model": "mxbai-embed-large:latest",
                "url": "http://127.0.0.1:11434"
              }
            },
            "llm": {
              "provider": "ollama",
              "config": {
                "model": "qwen3.5:9b",
                "url": "http://127.0.0.1:11434"
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }

## Summary

Add zero-cost pre-turn model routing: select the LLM based on keyword matching in the message before any LLM call.

## Motivation

Different tasks benefit from different models (coding → claude-sonnet, research → gemini-flash, quick Q&A → local qwen35). Currently requires manual /model switching.

## Proposed Design

Extend model.tasks with messageRouting:

```json5
{
  model: {
    primary: "vllm/qwen35",
    tasks: {
      messageRouting: {
        rules: [
          { match: ["code review", "PR", "diff"], model: "github-copilot/claude-sonnet-4.6" },
          { match: ["research", "search"], model: "gemini-3-flash" },
        ],
        default: "vllm/qwen35",
      },
    },
  },
}
```

- First-match-wins, case-insensitive substring matching
- Zero LLM cost — pure string matching
- Per-agent or defaults-level config
- Prototype implementation: scottgl9/openclaw feature/task-specific-models
